<br>
1) Option 1 - With PVP turned off, you cant harm other players.  This means you cannot throw a fireball in the middle of a combat if it would harm other players.  I really dont like that part of it.  I want players to be able to cast that fireball and unintentionally catch the rogue in the fight, etc..<br>
<br>
2) Option 2 - Everquest type, harmful spells just dont effect other players.  I don't think I like this either, being able to cast area spell after area spell into the middle of the fight without worrying about blasting your own party makes alot of things super easy.<br>
<br>
 <p>Segal
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#97694F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub26.ezboard.com/umaoudeib.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maoudeib</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Officer</span><br>  Posts: 862<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(5/31/01 12:32:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub26.ezboard.com/fapex71990frm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=76.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PVP</span><hr size=1> The main issue regarding PVP I think will have to do with combat situations.  With PVP turned on, you can accidentally attack a fellow player.  With area spells, this is a good limitation.  However, with melee against multiple targets this might not be to great.<br>
<br>
Not sure how targeting will work in NWN, but I found it a bit cumbersome in Baldur's Gate II.  I suspect in NWN targeting will be easier due to the better graphics and closer point of view.<br>
<br>
Overall I would say leave PVP on because it makes more sense.  For example, I won't be attacking a party member on purpose, but I might accidentally hit or cast on someone if I'm not careful.  Or as a caster I might only have a fireball left to cast and I decide to aim it behind the attacking goblins, hoping the fire will hit our enemies but not my friends...and I make a slight miscalculation...oops.<br>
<br>
Situations like this make the game more interesting I believe.<br>
<br>
-Robert<br>
 <p>Phantasmist Maob<BR>
Agnostic: Atypical Nonbeliever
