<br>
On a more practical note - i do not want the magic users thinking they can sit back and fireball or chain lightning every battle; with PVP on, they have to be more creative either with their timing, or with their spell choice.<br>
<br>
Archers are the same way, i think if they are firing into a large group, they should be able to hit that fat cleric standing in the fray thinking hes a tank.  This will also lead to more player communication (casting fireball, get out of the range of XX mob in 10 seconds) and maybe even some strategy building on the part of the players in terms of who goes where and when.<br>
